<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/388> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #388" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.31.1; Diod. 12.80.1; Chr. 354 (Cosso et Fiso); Degrassi 96, 374f. Postumius and Quinctius served under the Dictator against Veii (Liv. 4.40.4, and 41.10). On Quinctius, see Lübker no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/354> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #354" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Mommsen considers this to mean that this was the first authentic censorship (Str. 2.334f.). See 443, Censors." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/353> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #353" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Approved the Villa Publica in the Campus Martius and held the census there for the first time (Liv. 4.22.7).\n     Their term was limited to one and one-half years (Liv. 4.24.4-9; see 434). Cf. Liv. 9.33.7-9, and 34.9. See Degrassi 95, 370f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/311> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #311" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.12.1; Diod. 12.35.1; Chr. 354 (Fuso et Grasso); Fast. Hyd. (Pacilio et Crasso); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 95, 370f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/310> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #310" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Diod. Furius' praenomen is {Gr}, but Livy's C. is confirmed by 4.22.7, and 31.1. One cognomen appears as Pacilius in Liv. 4.12.1, cf. 22.7, and 52.1; but see Fast. Cap. on 251; {Gr} in Chr. Pasc.; the other as Fusus in Chr. 354, and {Gr} in Diod. Papirius' praenomen is M. in Liv. and {Gr} in Diod." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/281> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #281" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The Pontifex Maximus, traditions agree, presided over the election of Tribunes of the Plebs, but Livy (3.54.5) names Q. Furius, while Ascon. (77 C) names M. Papirius. On the names, see 441, Consuls." .
